).  At the top of the spiral staircase is a large platform with Grt. Spire Spirits (light blue to lvl60), 8 if I recall correctly with 1-2 roamers on the staircase.  Also on the platform is a Spire Lord (dark blue to lvl60).  Me being the cocky SK that I was tried to solo this Spire Lord, the fight was over rather quickly after I saw my chat box blur with hits for 145-175, and I saw that it Flurried.  These give good +faction with Sanctus Seru if you want to try and rise both city factions without destroying one of them.  =)<br><br>While roaming around I found a cave entrance on one of the zone walls, sorry I forget which and I wasn't able to find it again the other day.  Inside were the Thought Horrors, I believe they were all called Lesser Thought Horrors (green to lvl60).  They also had enthralled shik'nar type mobs in there.  Deep inside that cave complex was a Greater Thought Horror (dark blue to lvl60) and an Enthralled Hivemother (dark blue to lvl60).   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uepitomenegativity.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Epitome Negativity</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/4/02 11:48:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3706.topic&index=6>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How To: Rais your Sanctus Seru faction</span><hr size=1> I have allready obliterated my Katta faction, so my only other recourse is to try to repair my faction with Seru (tried to go Katta first).<br><br><br>I am kinda tired of killing Katta Guards, since im convinced the last 2 pieces of twink armor (legs or arms) wont ever drop (Validus Custodus Armor, +str, +hp, -agi)...<br><br>well... without some major assistance to kill the Crusaders...<br><br><br>More info on Katta Guards:<br><br>Legionnaires from Tenebrous Mountains (TM) to the Caster's Tower (CT) are pullable solo, but will assist if you engage melee within aggro of each other.<br><br>Legionnaires near the graveyard (GY) will allways assist on pulls.<br><br>Legionnaries on the bottom level allways assist on pulls (except near bar)<br><br>Crusaders allways assist on pulls.<br><br>Legionnaires from TM to CT are about 40% Light Blue, 60% Dark Blue (to level 51)<br><br>Legionnaires from the Guard Sonic Wolves to GY are all Dark Blue to level 51, and steadlily increase in level towards the GY.<br><br>Legionnaires in the GY courtyard are all near level 49, but never level 50 or more.<br><br>All Legionnaires on the bottom floor are about the same level as the ones in the GY courtyard, and the Dwarf/Gnome Legionnaires are very VERY resistant to Root/Snare.<br><br>Centurions can be found on the upper level only, near the Cathedral, and in the Warrior/Pally Guild (in GY courtyard).<br><br>Centurions can range in levels from 48 to 55+, and all levels share same spawnpoints.<br><br>Centurions level 50 or above WILL ALLWAYS summon, so be prepared.<br><br><br>At level 51...<br><br>Light Blue Legionnaires will drop with 1 BoD, and 1 Splurt.<br>Dark Blue Legionnaires (near TM) will drop with 1 BoD, 1 Splurt, and 1 Cascading Dark.<br>Dark Blue Legionnaires (near GY) will drop with 1 BoD, 1 EB, 1 Splurt, and 1 Cascading Dark. (prolly without dark, but they double/quad for 120's)<br><br><br><br><br>I hope this helps someone when hunting in Katta <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezb