ndex=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How To: Rais your Sanctus Seru faction</span><hr size=1> Something to thing of even though its probably minor...is there a reason to keep a Recuso or Spire spirit faction intact? Anybody who got kicked out of Sanctus Seru cant be all that bad a person considering the kind of facist types in Seru. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukelarnivmistweb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kelarniv Mistweb</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/4/02 5:33:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3706.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How To: Rais your Sanctus Seru faction</span><hr size=1> Recuso faction is used for some Katta Castellum quests (enemy of enemy is friend kind of deal). I don't think there's any point in keeping Spire Spirit faction, though. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uzorrco.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zorrco</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/4/02 11:44:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3706.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re: flipped factions</span><hr size=1> Epitome... I believe you have two factions backwards. Hand of Seru appears to be the outside guards (those who literally stand outside the zone like in Netherbain or Dawnshroud). They are also the Seru Guards you will see while in Marus Seru. Hand Legionnaires are the main guards you see on the inside of the zone (right after zoning in) to Sanctum Seru.<br><br>Tested that by killing both to see what faction hit came first. Also, if you're KoS in SS, you'll gain faction and notice &quot;bumps&quot; in faction improvement with every group - other than Hand Legionnaires. It seems they're either buggy or close to maxed KoS to some classes (I only killed one of each, remember).<br><br>Eye of Seru, in my experience, will be the first to max out. Perhaps KoS classes aren't KoS to with them to begin with? I'm not sure. All I know is after 600+ kills in Katta, I'm still KoS to Hand Legionnaires, Maxed ally with Eye of Seru and amiable to Hand of Seru (I haven't been inside to check the other factions yet).<br><br>On a side note, those 600 or so kills (and probably close to 100 helms) have me at amiable with Coterie as well.<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uskoobin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Skoobin</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://skoobin5881.homestead.com/files/v_anim.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/5/02 9:27:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3706.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re: flipped factions</span><hr size=1> Sooo...why not do Vamps Katta and Seru all allied?  Kill katta guards for vamp...seru guards for katta and then spire spirits for seru...will take 65 years but is possible theoretically <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utalmonious.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Talmonious</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/5/02 7:46:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3706.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re: flipped factions</span><hr size=1> It wouldn't work because you lose faction with all factions of the city you are killing in. (citizens faction comes to mind) You don't receive bonuses to citizen faction from killing in other cities to my knowledge. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uzorrco.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zorrco</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/6/02 4:29:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3706.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Won't work</span><hr size=1> Aye, it wouldn't work not only due to citizen faction, but the ONLY way (for now) known to raise Hand Legionnaire faction is by killing Katta guards.<br><br>Consider all the factions in Seru (some of whixh I'm sure I've yet to document):<br><br>Heart of Seru<br>Eye of Seru<br>Hand of Seru<br>Shoulders of Seru<br>Seru<br>Hand Legionnaires<br>Citizens of Seru<br><br><br>By making it so that you can only gain select factions in certain opposing areas, Verant has effectively prevented anyone from ever becoming non-Kos to Katta, Seru and Coterie simultaneously (providing they started KoS of course).<br><br>So you have two options - Cotherie and/or Seru or just Katta <br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uligge.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ligge</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_ball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/6/02 6:03:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3706.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Won't work</span><hr size=1> Actually you can get to nonKOS in both towns by killing in Seru and killing vampires. Then go hunt recluso and spire spites to fix Serus.<br><br>Just dont kill Legionarres while in Seru.<br><br>You dont take citizen faction hits in Seru so all is well. It seems the people dont much like or trust the oppressors anymore than I do! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uzorrco.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zorrco</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/8/02 12:44:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3706.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Won't work</span><hr size=1> Won't work. You TAKE a hit with Legionnaires when killing in Seru, but don't GET any when you kill Recluso or Spire Spirits - only by killing Katta guards.<br><br>I'll dig up my log and post the hits I got from 2 of the different guards.<br><br><br>Oh, and now after 650 kills, I've gone from scowling to threateningly to Hand Legionnaires... so life is improving <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br><br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showMessageRange?topicID=3706.topic&start=21&stop=34>2</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showPrevMessage?topicID=3706.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&